&lt;p&gt;Stripe is a financial infrastructure platform for businesses. Millions of companies—from the world’s largest enterprises to the most ambitious startups—use Stripe to accept payments, grow their revenue, and accelerate new business opportunities. Our mission is to increase the GDP of the internet, and we have a staggering amount of work ahead. That means you have an unprecedented opportunity to put the global economy within everyone’s reach while doing the most important work of your career.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About the organization&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Stripe Internal Systems owns the financial infrastructure and internal tools that Stripes runs on. You may work on a wide variety of critical business areas including:&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Financial platforms&lt;/strong&gt; used to track and understand all money movement at Stripe. We process trillions of dollars and leverage this data to meet the diverse needs of our business, supporting accounting in closing the books, and provide insights that guide investment and explain business performance.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Regulatory and tax&lt;/strong&gt; infrastructure used to invoice and collect tax from our customers. We deliver millions of invoices and thousands of regulatory and tax reports essential for Stripe to operate globally. We ensure compliance while enabling us to innovate and grow in new markets.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Seller and Marketing Systems &lt;/strong&gt;responsible for building the innovative tools and platforms that empower our Sellers and Marketers to bring in new business on Stripe platform as well as continue expanding services used by existing merchants on Stripe. As a member of this team, you&#39;ll develop cutting-edge solutions that turbo-charge productivity, and enable faster onboarding users on Stripe.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
